# --- Load Model Evaluation Results ---
def load_evaluation_results(directory, label):
    file_path = os.path.join(directory, "model_evaluation.csv")
    if os.path.exists(file_path):
        df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
        df['Model Type'] = label
        return df
    else:
        print(f" Evaluation file not found in: {file_path}")
        return pd.DataFrame()

tuned_df = load_evaluation_results("save/tune", "Tuned")

In[44]:
models = tuned_df['Model'].unique()
metrics = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1-score', 'Log Loss', 'ROC-AUC']

for model in models:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10), subplot_kw=dict(polar=True))
    model_data = combined_df[combined_df['Model'] == model]
    
    for index, row in model_data.iterrows():
        values = row[metrics].values.flatten().tolist()
        values += values[:1]
        angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, len(metrics), endpoint=False).tolist()
        angles += angles[:1]
        
        ax.plot(angles, values, label=f"{row['Model Type']}", linewidth=2)
        ax.fill(angles, values, alpha=0.25)

    ax.set_title(f'{model} Performance Metrics')
    ax.set_xticks(angles[:-1])
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)
    ax.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1.1))
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

desired_models = ["LeNet-5", "LeNet5-GRU", "VGG-16", "VGG16-GRU"]
In[88]:
for model_name in desired_models:  # Loop through each model
    # --- Filter Data for the current model ---
    model_df = combined_train_df[combined_train_df["Model"] == model_name]

    # Debug: Check if DataFrame is empty
    if len(model_df) == 0:
        print(f" Error: No data found for {model_name}. Check your CSV files.")
    else:
        # --- Plot Accuracy, Loss, Val-Accuracy, Val-Loss vs Epochs ---
        sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid")
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12))

        # --- 1. Accuracy vs Epochs ---
        for model_type, data in model_df.groupby("Model Type"):
            axes[0, 0].plot(data["Epoch"], data["Accuracy"], marker='o', label=model_type)
        axes[0, 0].set_title(f"{model_name}: Accuracy vs Epochs")  # Dynamic title
        axes[0, 0].set_xlabel("Epochs")
        axes[0, 0].set_ylabel("Accuracy")
        axes[0, 0].legend(loc="best")

        # --- 2. Loss vs Epochs ---
        for model_type, data in model_df.groupby("Model Type"):
            axes[0, 1].plot(data["Epoch"], data["Loss"], marker='o', label=model_type)
        axes[0, 1].set_title(f"{model_name}: Loss vs Epochs")  # Dynamic title
        axes[0, 1].set_xlabel("Epochs")
        axes[0, 1].set_ylabel("Loss")
        axes[0, 1].legend(loc="best")

        # --- 3. Validation Accuracy vs Epochs ---
        for model_type, data in model_df.groupby("Model Type"):
            axes[1, 0].plot(data["Epoch"], data["Val-accuracy"], marker='o', label=model_type)
        axes[1, 0].set_title(f"{model_name}: Validation Accuracy vs Epochs")  # Dynamic title
        axes[1, 0].set_xlabel("Epochs")
        axes[1, 0].set_ylabel("Validation Accuracy")
        axes[1, 0].legend(loc="best")

        # --- 4. Validation Loss vs Epochs ---
        for model_type, data in model_df.groupby("Model Type"):
            axes[1, 1].plot(data["Epoch"], data["Val-loss"], marker='o', label=model_type)
        axes[1, 1].set_title(f"{model_name}: Validation Loss vs Epochs")  # Dynamic title
        axes[1, 1].set_xlabel("Epochs")
        axes[1, 1].set_ylabel("Validation Loss")
        axes[1, 1].legend(loc="best")

        # --- Adjust layout & Show ---
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
